'''Rocket Fizz''' is a [[Franchising|franchise]] [[Chain store|chain]] of stores in the United States specializing in [[soft drink|soda]], [[candy]], and novelty items.<ref name="WW"/><ref name="PM"/><ref name="CBS12"/><ref name="IM"/> The company markets a diverse variety of [[Candy|candie]]s and produces its own line of [[soft drink]]s with unique flavors.<ref name="PM"/><ref name="HP"/><ref name="RFP"/> Its flagship store, which opened in 2009, two years after the company was founded, was located in [[Camarillo, California]]<ref name="RF"/> but closed in 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vcstar.com/story/money/business/2019/01/18/ventura-microbrewery-seaward-brewing-open/2550089002/|title=Open and shut: Seaward Brewing ready to make waves with Ventura debut|first=|last=@VCSEats|website=Ventura County Star|accessdate=17 May 2019}}</ref> The company also markets candies that are rare to find or in limited production by various manufacturers, such as those that were popular during the 1960s to 1980s.<ref name="WW"/><ref name="BJ"/> As of November 2018, there are 90 Rocket Fizz store locations in the United States and one in [[Canada]].<ref name="RFL"/>

==Products==
Rocket Fizz specializes in candy and soft drink products. For example, the franchise store in Beaverton, Oregon markets over 4,000 varieties of candy and over 500 varieties of soda drinks.<ref name="Oregonian"/> The company's franchise store in Cary, North Carolina markets over 1,200 varieties of candy and over 430 varieties of soft drinks.<ref name="BJ"/> Some of the company's beverages have been described as "novelty soft drinks".<ref name="PC"/>

The company's soda products are marketed with the brand name Rocket Fizz.<ref name="HP"/> A popular soda they produce is a [[bacon soda]], which is also named "Bacon Soda".<ref name="PM"/> At the company's Denver, Colorado store, bacon soda was described as the store's best-selling soda in 2012.<ref name="PM"/> The variety of soft drinks offered by Rocket Fizz has been described by ''Indianapolis Monthly'' magazine as "overwhelming", and the quantity of candies offered was described as "copious amounts".<ref name="IM"/>

In 2017, the chain began rollout of a line of sodas as part of a marketing deal with the band KISS; as of September 2017, the line consisted of Destroyer Kola, KISS Army root beer and Rock And Roll Over Cherry Kola.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://rocketfizz.com/products/kiss-sodas/|title=KISS Sodas  -  Rocket Fizz|website=rocketfizz.com|accessdate=13 September 2018}}</ref>

Rocket Fizz also produces [[ranch dressing]]-flavored soda,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://rocketfizz.com/news/9-newsflash/435-ranch-dressing-flavored-soda-could-be-the-worst-thing-on-the-planet|title='Ranch Dressing Flavored Soda Could Be The Worst Thing On The Planet!' - Rocket Fizz website|publisher=|accessdate=13 September 2018}}</ref> buffalo wing-flavored soda, coffee soda and one named dog drool, among others.<ref name="PM"/><ref name="CBS12"/>

The company also markets novelty items such as retro memorabilia and prank gifts.<ref name="Oregonian"/>

[[File:Portland Oregon Rocket Fizz Locaton.jpg|thumb|View inside the Portland Oregon Rocket Fizz location]]

==Locations== 
As of November 2018, there are 91 locations. Rocket Fizz has store locations in the U.S. states of [[Arizona]], [[Arkansas]], [[California]], [[Colorado]], [[Florida]], [[Georgia (U.S. state)|Georgia]], [[Illinois]], [[Indiana]], [[Iowa]], [[Kansas]], [[Louisiana]], [[Michigan]], [[Missouri]], [[Nebraska]], [[Nevada]], [[New Jersey]], [[New York (state)|New York]], [[North Carolina]], [[Ohio]], [[Oklahoma]], [[Oregon]], [[Pennsylvania]], [[South Carolina]], [[Tennessee]], [[Texas]], [[Utah]], [[Virginia]], [[Washington (state)|Washington]] and [[Wyoming]]. There is also one location in [[Alberta]], Canada.<ref name="WW"/><ref name="PM"/><ref name="Oregonian"/><ref name="RFL"/>

